radiographic_examinations.findings: Liver parenchyma appears within normal limits; no focal liver mass; main portal vein patent; no ascites; no intrahepatic biliary dilation; CBD measures 7.2 mm; 5 mm stone in gallbladder neck; several additional stones adjacent to neck; gallbladder wall mildly thickened (up to 4 mm); gallbladder not distended; no pericholecystic fluid; adenomyomatosis suggested.
